In a bowl, combine the first nine ingredients; mix well. Store in an airtight container in a cool dry place for up to 6 months. Yield: 3 batches (9 cups total) To prepare cookies: In a mixing bowl, cream butter. Add egg and molasses; mix well. add 3 cups cookie mix; beat until smooth. Shape into 1-in. balls and roll in sugar. Place 2 in. apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 375 degrees F for 9-11 minutes or until the edges are firm and the surface cracks. Cool on wire racks.